This product includes evaluation traces derived from AgentDojo, a benchmark for
prompt-injection attacks on tool-using LLM agents, by the ETH Zurich SPY Lab,
released under the MIT License (https://github.com/ethz-spylab/agentdojo). The
traces under fixtures/traces/ are generated from AgentDojo's task and injection
ground truth; the derivation is described in scripts/gen-fixtures/generate.py
and docs/spikes/agentdojo-fixture-feasibility.md.

The prior art on guardrail over-defense measurement that this project builds on
and cites — NotInject/InjecGuard, OR-Bench, XSTest, Meta CyberSecEval's False
Refusal Rate, and BELLS-O — is credited in the README.
